        <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #f6861f;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you update an existing project's <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet14">filtering </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet15">flattening </MadCap:conditionalText>settings, the settings will be dynamically updated when you close the Project Properties dialog. You do not need to update the Lingo project to apply the new <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet14">filtering </MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Snippets.Snippet15">flattening </MadCap:conditionalText>settings. However, if there are topics open when you make changes to these settings, you will need to close and reopen the topics before the new settings are applied.</p>
